what the hell wrong with my puppy wont be left on its own atall never starts barking and crying otherwise your puppy is experiencing separation anxiety dogs are pack animals and you are your puppy's pack leader when you leave he she becomes distressed many puppies and dogs with separation anxiety will bark and cry excessively and some even become destructive tearing up furniture and other belongings of yours to surround themselves in something that smells like you it makes them feel more comfortable i would recommend having little sessions of separating yourself from him her couple minutes at a time do not return when he starts barking if you return every time they will learn that you return when they bark you want to wean them off of having you around start off with little sessions of away time and work your way up also leave toys out to let them occupy themselves with and reward them with treats everytime you leave and comeback without a fuss Dog training Dog Skinny Puppy Socialization Hush Puppies Breastfeeding Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Basset Hound Anxiety Lady and the Tramp Fancy rat Crate training Cat Combat stress reaction Border Terrier Hamster Clinical depression One Tree Hill (TV series) Belgian Shepherd Dog Equilibrium (2002 film) Traumatic incident reduction Fox hunting Carl Barks Sick Puppy Diazepam Friends Zoophilia Police dog Spanking Puppy mill Panic attack Harry Nilsson Maltese (dog) Shetland Sheepdog Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Anorexia nervosa Animal testing Excel Saga The Dunciad Beagle Shaggy dog story Post-traumatic stress disorder Atal Bihari Vajpayee Scooby-Doo Brian Griffin Black Pete 101 Dalmatians: The Series Nintendogs The Amber Spyglass Spike (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Obedience training Urinary incontinence Alaskan husky Psychoanalysis Beethoven (film) Rabies EastEnders Traumatic brain injury Agoraphobia Rottweiler American Eskimo Dog Strap-on dildo Beast Wars Hypoglycemia Havanese Spot the Dog